<h3>The Current Search Model</h3>
<p>The problem with the current interface is that it inherits from traditional search engines such as <a href="http://google.com">Google</a> and is optimized for showing the most recent results. The small size of a tweet makes it incredibly difficult to estimate the relevance, which would normally be relatively straight-forward with traditional ranking algorithms. The interface does not favour towards metadata such as location, original tweets/re-tweets, documents within tweets, sentiment analysis or exploration of results.</p>
